sample_data_processing: The ATAC-seq reads were aligned to the hg19 human reference genome using the BWA aligner (Li and Durbin, 2010) ., Mapped reads were further converted to “bigWig” files counting reads in non-overlapping 200-bp windows across the genome using BEDTools for presentation as genome browser tracks  (Quinlan et al, 2010).This is the raw bigwigs., AtacWorks was used to denoise and improve the signal-to-noise ratio.
